{"title":"Wolf Tooth adds Oval & 3-Bolt T-Type Chainrings (and a Complete Compatibility Guide)","link":"https://bikerumor.com/wolf-tooth-adds-oval-3-bolt-t-type-chainrings-and-a-complete-compatibility-guide/","date":1689276176000,"content":"<p>Wolf Tooth recently <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wolf-tooth-adds-sram-t-type-drop-stop-chainrings/\" target=\"_blank\">announced their first batch</a> of SRAM Transmission T-Type compatible Drop Stop chainrings that fit the latest 8-bolt SRAM DUB Wide cranksets. Now, they’re adding 8-Bolt Oval Drop Stop B chainrings that fit the new T-Type Flat Top MTB chains for riders that like oval chainrings, and they’re working on 3-Bolt versions of all these for riders who want to use their existing SRAM or compatible cranks.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Perhaps best of all, they’ve <a href=\"https://www.avantlink.com/click.php?tt=cl&amp;mi=18985&amp;pw=293233&amp;ctc=&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wolftoothcomponents.com%2Fcollections%2Fmountain%2Fproducts%2Foval-direct-mount-chainrings-for-sram-8-bolt-mountain-cranks\" target=\"_blank\">made a comprehensive guide</a> to which T-Type chainrings fit which cranks and how to choose the right option, whether it’s the newer or older SRAM MTB cranks or a 3rd party crankset that used SRAM’s 3-bolt mounting standard.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>New T-Type Oval Chainrings</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/wolf-tooth-drop-stop-B-oval-chainring-for-sram-transmission-t-type-1.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1017\" height=\"568\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/wolf-tooth-drop-stop-B-oval-chainring-for-sram-transmission-t-type-1.jpg\" alt=\"Wolf Tooth 8-bolt direct mount chainrings for SRAM T-Type Flattop MTB chains\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/wolf-tooth-drop-stop-B-oval-chainring-for-sram-transmission-t-type-1.jpg 1017w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/wolf-tooth-drop-stop-B-oval-chainring-for-sram-transmission-t-type-1-297x166.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/wolf-tooth-drop-stop-B-oval-chainring-for-sram-transmission-t-type-1-800x447.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/wolf-tooth-drop-stop-B-oval-chainring-for-sram-transmission-t-type-1-120x67.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/wolf-tooth-drop-stop-B-oval-chainring-for-sram-transmission-t-type-1-768x429.jpg 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Like the round ones that launched in June, the inital batch of <a href=\"https://www.avantlink.com/click.php?tt=cl&amp;mi=18985&amp;pw=293233&amp;ctc=&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wolftoothcomponents.com%2Fcollections%2Fmountain%2Fproducts%2Foval-direct-mount-chainrings-for-sram-8-bolt-mountain-cranks\" target=\"_blank\">Oval Drop Stop B T-Type</a> chainrings fit SRAM’s latest DUB Wide cranksets that come with Transmission groups and use the 8-bolt mounting standard.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Additionally, the updated Drop Stop B tooth profile has slightly thinner wide teeth and deeper valleys to accomodate the Flattop MTB chain’s larger rollers and narrower distance between outer plates. They’re also still compatible with standard SRAM Eagle chains, plus 12-speed chains from KMC, Connex, Wipperman, and Campagnolo. (They’re even compatible all 9/10/11 speed chains, too, if you’re rockin’ it old school)</p>\n\n\n\n<p>They’re available in 32 and 34 tooth counts with the 3mm offset for XO and GX Transmission groups, and a 0mm offset is coming soon for XX1 SL groups, all of which maintain the desired 55mm chainline. MSRP is $75-85.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>T-Type Compatible 3-Bolt Drop Stop B Chainrings, too!</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/wolf-tooth-drop-stop-B-3-bolt-chainring-for-sram-transmission-t-type-2.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1800\" height=\"1201\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/wolf-tooth-drop-stop-B-3-bolt-chainring-for-sram-transmission-t-type-2.jpg\" alt=\"Wolf Tooth 3-bolt direct mount chainrings for SRAM T-Type Flattop MTB chains\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/wolf-tooth-drop-stop-B-3-bolt-chainring-for-sram-transmission-t-type-2.jpg 1800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/wolf-tooth-drop-stop-B-3-bolt-chainring-for-sram-transmission-t-type-2-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/wolf-tooth-drop-stop-B-3-bolt-chainring-for-sram-transmission-t-type-2-800x534.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/wolf-tooth-drop-stop-B-3-bolt-chainring-for-sram-transmission-t-type-2-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/wolf-tooth-drop-stop-B-3-bolt-chainring-for-sram-transmission-t-type-2-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/wolf-tooth-drop-stop-B-3-bolt-chainring-for-sram-transmission-t-type-2-1536x1025.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/wolf-tooth-drop-stop-B-3-bolt-chainring-for-sram-transmission-t-type-2-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Got an older SRAM crankset that you’d like to keep and run with the new Transmission cassette and derailleur? Now you can, and there’ll be even more options in August.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Until now, Wolf Tooth’s 3-bolt direct mount chainrings used their Drop Stop A or ST tooth profiles, the former working with SRAM Eagle groups and the latter specifically for Shimano’s latest 12-speed MTB groups.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/wolf-tooth-drop-stop-B-3-bolt-chainring-for-sram-transmission-t-type-1.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1039\" height=\"590\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/wolf-tooth-drop-stop-B-3-bolt-chainring-for-sram-transmission-t-type-1.jpg\" alt=\"Wolf Tooth 3-bolt direct mount chainrings for SRAM T-Type Flattop MTB chains\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/wolf-tooth-drop-stop-B-3-bolt-chainring-for-sram-transmission-t-type-1.jpg 1039w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/wolf-tooth-drop-stop-B-3-bolt-chainring-for-sram-transmission-t-type-1-297x169.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/wolf-tooth-drop-stop-B-3-bolt-chainring-for-sram-transmission-t-type-1-800x454.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/wolf-tooth-drop-stop-B-3-bolt-chainring-for-sram-transmission-t-type-1-120x68.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/wolf-tooth-drop-stop-B-3-bolt-chainring-for-sram-transmission-t-type-1-768x436.jpg 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Now, they’ve added <a href=\"https://www.avantlink.com/click.php?tt=cl&amp;mi=18985&amp;pw=293233&amp;ctc=&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wolftoothcomponents.com%2Fcollections%2Fmountain%2Fproducts%2Fdirect-mount-chainrings-for-sram-cranks\" target=\"_blank\">3-Bolt Drop Stop B versions</a> that’ll work with the Flattop MTB chains (and, thus, Transmission), too. The initial batch comes in 3mm offsets, and 0mm offsets are coming in August. Check that <a href=\"https://www.avantlink.com/click.php?tt=cl&amp;mi=18985&amp;pw=293233&amp;ctc=&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wolftoothcomponents.com%2Fpages%2Fhow-to-find-the-correct-chainring-for-your-mountain-bike-with-sram-transmission\" target=\"_blank\">compatibility guide</a> to see which ones you’ll need.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Wolf-tooth-CAMO-chainring-for-Flattop-MTB-chains.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1188\" height=\"792\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Wolf-tooth-CAMO-chainring-for-Flattop-MTB-chains.jpg\" alt=\"Wolf Tooth CAMO chainrings with T-Type compatible tooth profiles\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Wolf-tooth-CAMO-chainring-for-Flattop-MTB-chains.jpg 1188w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Wolf-tooth-CAMO-chainring-for-Flattop-MTB-chains-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Wolf-tooth-CAMO-chainring-for-Flattop-MTB-chains-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Wolf-tooth-CAMO-chainring-for-Flattop-MTB-chains-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Wolf-tooth-CAMO-chainring-for-Flattop-MTB-chains-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Wolf-tooth-CAMO-chainring-for-Flattop-MTB-chains-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>They’ve also updated their <a href=\"https://www.avantlink.com/click.php?tt=cl&amp;mi=18985&amp;pw=293233&amp;ctc=&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wolftoothcomponents.com%2Fcollections%2Fcamo\" target=\"_blank\">CAMO chainrings</a> to work with Flattop MTB chains, too, giving you all the options for updating your existing cranksets to work with the new SRAM Transmission.</p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wolf-tooth-adds-oval-3-bolt-t-type-chainrings-and-a-complete-compatibility-guide/\">Wolf Tooth adds Oval &amp; 3-Bolt T-Type Chainrings (and a Complete Compatibility Guide)</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Tyler Benedict","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"d52b2b6901ca8e5d74cdaa5e3cd5314249b949ab95c2bd40f6bfe15a1aecdabe","category":"Cycling"}